\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is invertible, so 
\begin_inset Formula $C(A)$
\end_inset

 is all of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{4}$
\end_inset

.
 So any 4 linearly independent vectors work, e.g.
 the columns of 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $D$
\end_inset

, or simply the Cartesian basis (the columns of the 
\begin_inset Formula $4\times4$
\end_inset

 identity matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $I$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

